title: Stacey Abrams
added: After the victory of [[Joe Biden]] in the [[2020 United States presidential election|2020 US Presidential election]], both ''The New York Times'' and ''The Washington Post'' wrote that Abrams was credited with the large boost to Democratic votes in Georgia, inspiring an estimated 800,000 new voter registrations.<ref>{{cite news| url = https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/06/us/politics/stacey-abrams-georgia.html| title = As Biden Inches Ahead in Georgia, Stacey Abrams Draws Recognition and Praise | author = Hakim, Danny; Saul, Stephanie; Thrush, Glenn| date = November 6, 2020| accessdate = November 9, 2020|newspaper = The New York Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/stacey-abrams-credited-for-boosting-democrats-in-georgia/2020/11/08/e93518b6-21ef-11eb-9c4a-0dc6242c4814_story.html| title = Stacey Abrams credited for boosting Democrats in Georgia| author = Barrow, Bill; Stafford, Kat| date = November 8, 2020| accessdate = November 9, 2020|newspaper = The Washington Post}}</ref>
